History: Evaluation of the patient with urosepsis.
Findings: Portable AP radiograph of the chest was reviewed in comparison to. Right internal jugular line tip is currently low, at the level of the right atrium and should be pulled back approximately 23 cm. There is interval placement of the right nephrostomy, partially imaged. Pulmonary edema is still present, although minimally improved since the prior study. Right middle lobe atelectasis and left retrocardiac density with air bronchogram persist, highly worrisome for pneumonia.
